When a user exceeds their query limit the API rejects requests and returns an error (HTTP 429). Typical responses include:

- A 429 response with a JSON body like:
  {
    "success": false,
    "error": "Monthly query limit exceeded",
    "usage": {
      "current": 101,
      "max": 100,
      "exceeded": true,
      "reset_at": "2026-02-01T00:00:00Z"
    }
  }
  This shows current vs. max usage and the monthly reset time.

- Some endpoints return a rate-limit error object:
  {
    "error": {
      "code": "RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED",
      "message": "Rate limit exceeded. Try again in 60 seconds"
    }
  }

- In credit-based cases you may see an INSUFFICIENT_CREDITS error:
  {
    "error": {
      "code": "INSUFFICIENT_CREDITS",
      "message": "Need 5000 credits, have 5000"
    }
  }

Responses also include rate-limit headers (X-RateLimit-Limit, X-RateLimit-Remaining, X-RateLimit-Reset) indicating when you can retry. Common remedies are to wait until the reset time or upgrade your plan.

When a user exceeds their query limit the API returns a 429 (Too Many Requests) and includes rate-limit details so the client can react.

Typical behaviors:
- Monthly query limit exceeded:
  - Response example:
    {
      "success": false,
      "error": "Monthly query limit exceeded",
      "usage": {
        "current": 101,
        "max": 100,
        "exceeded": true,
        "reset_at": "2026-02-01T00:00:00Z"
      }
    }
  - The usage object shows current, max (−1 means unlimited), whether exceeded, and the monthly reset timestamp.

- Per-minute (rate) limit exceeded:
  - Response example:
    {
      "error": {
        "code": "RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED",
        "message": "Rate limit exceeded. Try again in 60 seconds"
      }
    }
  - Responses also include rate-limit headers on every response:
    X-RateLimit-Limit, X-RateLimit-Remaining, X-RateLimit-Reset (seconds until reset).

Recommended handling: check the headers, implement exponential backoff on 429s, cache responses to avoid duplicate queries, and batch requests where possible.
